label.value: Encounter due to Problems Related to Alleged Sexual Abuse of Child by Person Outside Primary Support Group

value.value: An ICD encounter due to problems related to alleged sexual abuse of child by person outside primary support group, including problems related to contact or attempted contact with the child's or the other person's breasts or genitals, sexual exposure in close confrontation or attempt to undress or seduce the child, by a substantially older person outside the child's family, either on the basis of this person's position or status or against the will of the child.

label.value: Encounter due to Problems Related to Alleged Physical Abuse of Child

value.value: An ICD encounter due to problems related to alleged physical abuse of child, including problems related to incidents in which the child has been injured in the past by any adult in the household to a medically significant extent (e.g. fractures, marked bruising) or that involved abnormal forms of violence (e.g. hitting the child with hard or sharp implements, burning or tying up of the child).

label.value: Encounter due to Personal Frightening Experience in Childhood

value.value: An ICD encounter due to personal frightening experience in childhood, including experience carrying a threat for the child's future, such as a kidnapping, natural disaster with a threat to life, injury with a threat to self-image or security, or witnessing a severe trauma to a loved one.

label.value: Encounter due to Other Negative Life Events in Childhood

value.value: An ICD encounter due to other negative life events in childhood.

label.value: Encounter due to Negative Life Event in Childhood, Unspecified

value.value: An ICD encounter due to negative life event in childhood, unspecified.

label.value: Encounter due to Other Problems Related to Upbringing

value.value: An ICD encounter due to other problems related to upbringing, excluding maltreatment syndromes (T74.-).

label.value: Encounter due to Inadequate Parental Supervision and Control

value.value: An ICD encounter due to inadequate parental supervision and control, including lack of parental knowledge of what the child is doing or where the child is; poor control; lack of concern or lack of attempted intervention when the child is in risky situations.

label.value: MDM2 Gene

value.value: This gene plays a role in several cellular processes related to cellular viability; including the cell cycle and apoptosis.

label.value: Encounter due to Parental Overprotection

value.value: An ICD encounter due to parental overprotection, including pattern of upbringing resulting in infantilization and prevention of independent behavior.

label.value: Encounter due to Institutional Upbringing

value.value: An ICD encounter due to institutional upbringing, including group foster care in which parenting responsibilities are largely taken over by some form of institution (such as residential nursery, orphanage, or children's home), or therapeutic care over a prolonged period in which the child is in a hospital, convalescent home or the like, without at least one parent living with the child.

label.value: Encounter due to Hostility Towards and Scapegoating of Child

value.value: An ICD encounter due to hostility towards and scapegoating of child, including negative parental behavior specifically focused on the child as an individual, persistent over time and pervasive over several child behaviors (e.g. automatically blaming the child for any problems in the household or attributing negative characteristics to the child).

label.value: Encounter due to Emotional Neglect of Child

value.value: An ICD encounter due to emotional neglect of child, including parent talking to the child in a dismissive or insensitive way. lack of interest in the child, of sympathy for the child's difficulties and of praise and encouragement. irritated reaction to anxious behavior and absence of sufficient physical comforting and emotional warmth.

label.value: Encounter due to Other Problems Related to Neglect in Upbringing

value.value: An ICD encounter due to other problems related to neglect in upbringing, including lack of learning and play experience.

label.value: Encounter due to Inappropriate Parental Pressure and Other Abnormal Qualities of Upbringing

value.value: An ICD encounter due to inappropriate parental pressure and other abnormal qualities of upbringing, including parents forcing the child to be different from the local norm, either sex-inappropriate (e.g. dressing a boy in girl's clothes), age-inappropriate (e.g. forcing a child to take on responsibilities above her or his own age) or otherwise inappropriate (e.g. pressing the child to engage in unwanted or too difficult activities).

label.value: Encounter due to Other Specified Problems Related to Upbringing

value.value: An ICD encounter due to other specified problems related to upbringing.

label.value: Encounter due to Problem Related to Upbringing, Unspecified

value.value: An ICD encounter due to problem related to upbringing, unspecified.

label.value: Encounter due to Other Problems Related to Primary Support Group, Including Family Circumstances

value.value: An ICD encounter due to other problems related to primary support group, including family circumstances, excluding maltreatment syndromes (T74.-), problems related to: negative life events in childhood (Z61.-), upbringing (Z62.-).

label.value: Encounter due to Problems in Relationship with Spouse Or Partner

value.value: An ICD encounter due to problems in relationship with spouse or partner, including discord between partners resulting in severe or prolonged loss of control, in generalization of hostile or critical feelings or in a persisting atmosphere of severe interpersonal violence (hitting or striking).

label.value: NOTCH4 Gene

value.value: This gene plays a regulatory role in vascular, renal and hepatic development.

label.value: Encounter due to Problems in Relationship with Parents and In-Laws

value.value: An ICD encounter due to problems in relationship with parents and in-laws.

label.value: Encounter due to Inadequate Family Support

value.value: An ICD encounter due to inadequate family support.

label.value: Encounter due to Absence of Family Member

value.value: An ICD encounter due to absence of family member.

label.value: Encounter due to Disappearance and Death of Family Member

value.value: An ICD encounter due to disappearance and death of family member, including assumed death of family member.

label.value: Encounter due to Disruption of Family by Separation and Divorce

value.value: An ICD encounter due to disruption of family by separation and divorce, including estrangement.

label.value: Encounter due to Dependent Relative Needing Care At Home

value.value: An ICD encounter due to dependent relative needing care at home.

label.value: Encounter due to Other Stressful Life Events Affecting Family and Household

value.value: An ICD encounter due to other stressful life events affecting family and household, including anxiety (normal) about sick person in family, health problems within family, ill or disturbed family member, isolated family.

label.value: Encounter due to Other Specified Problems Related to Primary Support Group

value.value: An ICD encounter due to other specified problems related to primary support group, including family discord not otherwise specified, high expressed emotional level within family, inadequate or distorted communication within family.

label.value: Encounter due to Problem Related to Primary Support Group, Unspecified

value.value: An ICD encounter due to problem related to primary support group, unspecified.

label.value: Encounter due to Problems Related to Unwanted Pregnancy

value.value: An ICD encounter due to problems related to unwanted pregnancy, excluding supervision of high-risk pregnancy due to social problems (Z35.7).

label.value: EIF3E Gene

value.value: This gene is involved in the initiation and regulation of protein translation.

label.value: Encounter due to Problems Related to Multiparity

value.value: An ICD encounter due to problems related to multiparity, excluding supervision of pregnancy with grand multiparity (Z35.4).

label.value: Encounter due to Seeking and Accepting Physical, Nutritional and Chemical Interventions Known to be Hazardous and Harmful

value.value: An ICD encounter due to seeking and accepting physical, nutritional and chemical interventions known to be hazardous and harmful, excluding substance dependence - see Alphabetical Index.

label.value: Encounter due to Seeking and Accepting Behavioral and Psychological Interventions Known to be Hazardous and Harmful

value.value: An ICD encounter due to seeking and accepting behavioral and psychological interventions known to be hazardous and harmful.

label.value: Encounter due to Discord with Counselors

value.value: An ICD encounter due to discord with counselors, including discord with probation officer, social worker.

label.value: Encounter due to Problems Related to Other Psychosocial Circumstances

value.value: An ICD encounter due to problems related to other psychosocial circumstances, excluding current injury - see Alphabetical Index.

label.value: Encounter due to Conviction in Civil and Criminal Proceedings without Imprisonment

value.value: An ICD encounter due to conviction in civil and criminal proceedings without imprisonment.

label.value: Encounter due to Imprisonment and Other Incarceration

value.value: An ICD encounter due to imprisonment and other incarceration.

label.value: Encounter due to Problems Related to Release from Prison

value.value: An ICD encounter due to problems related to release from prison.

label.value: Encounter due to Problems Related to Other Legal Circumstances

value.value: An ICD encounter due to problems related to other legal circumstances, including arrest, child custody or support proceedings, litigation, prosecution.

label.value: Encounter due to Victim of Crime and Terrorism

value.value: An ICD encounter due to victim of crime and terrorism, including victim of torture.

label.value: Oncogene KIT

value.value: Cloned cancer gene for Familial gastrointestinal stromal tumors (GIST), KIT proto-oncogene encodes a putative transmembrane receptor tyrosine kinase for stem cell factor and is critical in the development of pluripotent hematopoietic stem cells, migrating embryonic melanoblasts, and primordial germ cells.  The human proto-oncogene is located at 4q12.

label.value: Encounter due to Exposure to Disaster, War and Other Hostilities

value.value: An ICD encounter due to exposure to disaster, war and other hostilities, excluding target of perceived discrimination or persecution (Z60.5).

label.value: Encounter due to Other Specified Problems Related to Psychosocial Circumstances

value.value: An ICD encounter due to other specified problems related to psychosocial circumstances.

label.value: Encounter due to Problem Related to Unspecified Psychosocial Circumstances

value.value: An ICD encounter due to problem related to unspecified psychosocial circumstances.

label.value: Combination Route of Administration

value.value: Administration of a drug by more than one route at the same time.

label.value: Perfusion Route of Administration

value.value: The use of the circulatory system to deliver a drug to an organ or tissue.

label.value: Translingual Route of Administration

value.value: The administration of a drug to the surface of the tongue.

label.value: Base of the Eyelashes Route of Administration

value.value: The topical administration of a drug to the base of the eyelashes.

label.value: Administration via Central Line Irrigation

value.value: The administration of a drug by central line irrigation.

label.value: Cervical Route of Administration

value.value: The administration of a drug to the cervix uteri.
